headline: General Mills Guidance Reset And Leadership Change Put Execution In Focus
summary: General Mills (NYSE:GIS) cut its full year fiscal 2026 sales and earnings guidance, pointing to weaker consumer sentiment and more volatile category demand. The company framed the guidance reset as a response to recent trading conditions and a reassessment of near term expectations. Former Chief Information Officer Donald Monk left General Mills to join Hormel Foods, marking a change in senior leadership during this period. headline: General Mills to Webcast Fiscal 2026 Third Quarter Earnings Results on March 18, 2026
summary: MINNEAPOLIS, February 25, 2026--General Mills, Inc. (NYSE: GIS) plans to report results for its fiscal 2026 third quarter on March 18, 2026.
